human_system_low,electrical hum,814061,ELECMisc-INT_NOISES-Electrical Hums And Crackles Of A Light Fixture With A Loose Light Bulb_YMLT_NONE_08982261,"buzz, crackle, electric, electrical, electricity, fluorescent, hum, light, pop","An isolated sound capture of my broken light fixture from my ceiling light. Various change-ups of electrical hums and crackles. Taken around ~4cm from the light. If boosted to max there is probably unwanted Noise in the recording as I live in a busy part of town, otherwise it's a pretty clean recording.

<strong>I have marked it as Creative Commons 0.</strong> Feel free to attribute me, but it's not required. Enjoy!

<u>Recordist Note:</u>
*Sorry for any unisolated sounds, It was an impromptu recording, because my light rarely does this!
*For the sake of versatility and quality, I have kept it unedited, only trimmed.

Recorded June 26th, 2025. On a TASCAM Portacapture X6 (XY pattern, Field Record preset, NO Radius Deadcat applied) with <b>no post-processing.</b> Only trimming.

<u><b>Timestamps</b></u>
None


I'm always happy to chat and always learning and curious! If you have any questions, especially about where and how I capture my sounds, feel free to shoot me a private message.

If you'd like to support Freesound and help them keep this amazing resource ad-free, you can make a donation <a href=""https://freesound.org/donations/donate/"" rel=""nofollow"">here</a>. Every contribution, big or small, is greatly appreciated.

<i>Your feedback is greatly appreciated, whether praise or constructive criticism.</i>

<i><b>For the best audio quality, I recommend downloading the files.</b></i>

To show your appreciation for my work, consider sharing your finished product! You can DM me about the work, or leave a comment in the sound(s) you used with a link to the related work. Briefly mention that my sound was included in your project. It's always inspiring to see how my sounds come to life in different contexts.
Of course, it is always appreciated to credit me for <b>Creative Commons 0</b> but <i>not required</i> and for <b>Attribution/NonCommercial 4.0</b> it is <i>required</i>.

I hope you enjoy my sound! I'm eager to see how you use them in your creative projects. Thank you!",http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/,wav,10.6029,YouMightLikeThis,323,4.7,2025-06-29T22:23:02Z,4075592,0,32,48000.0,2,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/814/814061_16787921-hq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/814/814061_16787921-lq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/814/814061_16787921_spec_M.jpg,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/814/814061_16787921_wave_M.png,https://freesound.org/people/YouMightLikeThis/sounds/814061/,7,128.0,,53.523,0.0,1.0,0.001,54.395,9.473,,True
