Feel free to adjust the description to better suit your style and the specific qualities of your sounds.",http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/,wav,3.58077,Smokeyeyebeats,49,5.0,2024-03-05T16:48:47Z,947684,0,24,44100.0,2,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/726/726228_15762055-hq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/726/726228_15762055-lq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/726/726228_15762055_spec_M.jpg,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/726/726228_15762055_wave_M.png,https://freesound.org/people/Smokeyeyebeats/sounds/726228/,78,101.0,,1910.295,6.724,0.609,0.093,65.43,2.931,,True
human_system_low,transformer hum,712564,AMBDsgn_Server room.Data center.Machine And Vent noise.Wide.Designed_EM,"ambience, ambient, artificial, atmo, atmosphere, background, computer, control-room, data, data-center, designed, digital, electronic, environment, future, general-noise, hitech, interior, machine, machine-room, noise, room, room-tone, sci-fi, server, server-room, space, spaceship, technology, ventilation","Background noise to create the basis for the atmosphere of technological spaces. Made from a sound recording from a transformer substation. The recording was made on a quiet night. In the recording, in the background there is noise from a city boiler room, which resembles the noise of fans and ventilation. The fundamental tone of the transformer hum, and the first few harmonics have been removed. Only the upper harmonics are left. Some resonances were also suppressed and the side component at high frequencies was equalized. In conclusion, the stereo panorama has been slightly expanded using an imager from OZONE. Has a tuned loop.",https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/,wav,18.0637,newlocknew,891,4.764705882352941,2023-11-27T09:43:28Z,3469052,0,16,48000.0,2,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/712/712564_5828667-hq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/712/712564_5828667-lq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/712/712564_5828667_spec_M.jpg,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/712/712564_5828667_wave_M.png,https://freesound.org/people/newlocknew/sounds/712564/,79,94.0,,98.242,1.588,1.0,0.004,37.78,17.028,,True
human_system_low,transformer hum,844244,Electric Failure – High Voltage Power Down #2 ATP2 (CC0),"ai-generated, drone, electric, electronic, failure, glitch, industrial, machine, malfunction, power-down, sfx, shutdown","Macro
Electric failure / high-voltage transformer-style shutdown sound effect.

Meso
Begins with a sharp, high-frequency electrical drone suggesting overload or unstable current. The tone abruptly destabilizes and collapses into a lower-frequency, decaying power-down tail. Single non-looping event designed to communicate malfunction rather than intentional shutdown.

Micro (Sonic Characteristics)
- Envelope: Immediate high-energy onset, abrupt drop, followed by short decaying tail
- Pitch behavior: High sustained tone that breaks and falls into lower register
- Texture: Noise-dominant electrical buzz with glitch-like instability
- Timbre: Bright, piercing upper frequencies transitioning to darker low-end hum
- Dynamics: Strong initial presence with rapid energy collapse
- Stereo image: Centered, stable
- Noise floor: Clean digital render

Technical / AI Disclosure
- Generation service: ElevenLabs Sound Effects Generator
- Model: ElevenLabs Legacy Sound Effects Model
- Access type: Paid subscription
- Exact prompt used: ""Electric failure, High Voltage Transformer power down""
- Post-processing: None

Ownership &amp; Rights
Generated under a paid ElevenLabs subscription. Under the subscription terms active at the time of creation, the output is licensed for commercial use by the subscriber. No third-party copyrighted material was sampled or incorporated. Uploaded under CC0 by the generating subscriber.

Purpose / Use Cases
Suitable for machinery malfunction cues, industrial system failure, sci-fi power collapse, dramatic tension moments, game events, theatre transitions, and cinematic shutdown sequences.

Sample used as riser, slowed down and reversed: <a href=""https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nm1CKG8CkDQ&amp;t=152s"" rel=""nofollow"">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nm1CKG8CkDQ&amp;t=152s</a>",http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/,wav,2.08981,ATP2-kh,178,4.333333333333333,2026-02-04T22:56:24Z,401322,0,16,48000.0,2,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/844/844244_18042200-hq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/844/844244_18042200-lq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/844/844244_18042200_spec_M.jpg,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/844/844244_18042200_wave_M.png,https://freesound.org/people/ATP2-kh/sounds/844244/,80,148.0,,1050.92,9.598,0.902,0.029,63.68,1.375,,True
