bird_presence_unit,single bird chirp,744721,Thunder 06,"field-recording, lightning, nature, sound-design, storm, thunder, thunder-storm, thunderstorm, weather","Clear recording of single thunder sound during a small storm. I got very lucky when recording these since the rain had already passed but the thunder sounds could still be heard clearly in my back yard.

Recorded on the Zoom H5 using Zoom's SGH-6 shotgun mic capsule and a Sennheiser MKE 600 microphone. The two recordings have been panned left-right for a stereo sound and processed in Reaper to reduce noise and remove unwanted sounds such as bird chirps and wind while still preserving good audio quality.",http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/,wav,10.1041,Emulius,229,4.875,2024-07-05T12:56:31Z,2910660,0,24,48000.0,2,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/744/744721_10934718-hq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/previews/744/744721_10934718-lq.mp3,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/744/744721_10934718_spec_M.jpg,https://cdn.freesound.org/displays/744/744721_10934718_wave_M.png,https://freesound.org/people/Emulius/sounds/744721/,162,,,,,,,,,429 Client Error: Too Many Requests for url: https://freesound.org/apiv2/sounds/744721/analysis/?token=bMrT43PW9ydzLChruivbJD3CNg8uHXSh0D7s1YLl,False
